abstract: Joe Biden hugged Barack Obama tightly as the former vice president came under attack from Bernie Sanders and Julián Castro. Elizabeth Warren went unscathed, while Kamala Harris stuck to a script.
snippet: Joe Biden hugged Barack Obama tightly as the former vice president came under attack from Bernie Sanders and Julián Castro. Elizabeth Warren went unscathed, while Kamala Harris stuck to a script.
lead_paragraph: Thursday’s Democratic primary debate was the first time all the leading candidates were onstage together. The most illuminating exchanges were not between Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Elizabeth Warren, who met onstage for the first time, but from other pairings. Here are six highlights from the debate.

abstract: Joe Biden, Kamala Harris, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren are the leading Democrats in the presidential primary. We take a look back at their debate performances.
snippet: Joe Biden, Kamala Harris, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren are the leading Democrats in the presidential primary. We take a look back at their debate performances.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Ahead of Thursday’s debate, we looked back at how the leading Democratic candidates — Joseph R. Biden Jr., Kamala Harris, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren — performed in the first two debates.

abstract: President Trump confirmed that he spoke with his secretary of state about also serving as national security adviser, and they ruled it out. But the discussion underscored Mr. Pompeo’s clout.
snippet: President Trump confirmed that he spoke with his secretary of state about also serving as national security adviser, and they ruled it out. But the discussion underscored Mr. Pompeo’s clout.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It took about five minutes after John R. Bolton’s unceremonious fall from grace this week before Washington’s official whisper factory started floating a surprising suggestion for a replacement: Mike Pompeo.

abstract: Everything you need to know about the presidential primary debate in Houston.
snippet: Everything you need to know about the presidential primary debate in Houston.
lead_paragraph: Quick, name the most substantive discussion of foreign policy you have heard during the nearly 10 hours of debates so far. Struggling? Yes, foreign affairs has played a minimal role so far in the Democratic primary debates but that could change on Thursday night.

abstract: The president’s odd reference to one of his children was comedic fodder for the late-night hosts. “At least Darth Vader claimed his son,” one said.

abstract: In a meme group, sardonic and sincere Williamson supporters unite against the haters.
snippet: In a meme group, sardonic and sincere Williamson supporters unite against the haters.
lead_paragraph: It began, like so many modern presidential campaign stories do, as a joke. Sarah Marilyn, a 28-year-old Brooklyn social media strategist, didn’t bother to watch the first Democratic debates in June. She was only vaguely aware that they were happening until the memes began cascading onto her phone. She chased the best jokes, fell into a kind of Photoshop fugue state, and emerged as the co-founder of a Facebook page dedicated to the candidate with the most stimulating content: Marianne Williamson’s Dank Meme Stash.
